    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Subjects admitted to hospital with systolic heart failure(LVEF under 45%) in 2009

          -  Subjects, age 20 or/and above

          -  Subjects admitted to hospital (emergency area, to internal medicine or to cardiology
             wards, CCU or intensive care) with dyspnea and verification of heart failure based on
             following criteria;

          -  Symptoms typical of heart failure : breathlessness at rest or on exercise, fatigue,
             tiredness, ankle swelling and Signs typical of heart failure : tachycardia,
             tachypnoea, pulmonary rales, pleural effusion, raised jugular venous pressure,
             peripheral oedema, hepatomegaly

          -  Objective evidence of a structural or functional abnormality of the heart at rest :
             cardiomegaly, third heard sound, cardiac murmurs, abnormality on the echocardiogram,
             raised natriuretic peptide concentration

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Subject who expired during hospitalization
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
